</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-Q&AMP;A-SPELLMAN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Q&AMP;A WITH ALONZO SPELLMAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cowboys defensive tackle Alonzo Spellman sat down and played
``20 Questions'' with Star-Telegram staff writer Ray Buck:
</P>
<P>
   1. You read the Bible every day. How old is your Bible and where
do you keep it?
</P>
<P>
   ``I've had a Bible all my life, but my present Bible is about 2
1/2 years old. I keep it on my bathroom vanity at home. And when I
travel, I always have it with me.''
</P>
<P>
   2. Your favorite Scripture?
</P>
<P>
   ``My favorite ``book'' in the Bible is the book of Psalms. It's
basically a book of prayers. I love Psalms. Certainly one of my
favorites, which is really a good one if you find yourself under
attack or fighting out of a hole, is Psalms 35.''
</P>
<P>
   3. The dirtiest player you've ever played against?
</P>
<P>
   ``Without a doubt, Steve Wisniewski of the Raiders. Kevin Gogan
\RDolphins\S is bad, too, but not as bad as Wisniewski. One time,
Wisniewski chopped me probably five or 10 seconds after the whistle
blew. Gogan's thing is to taunt you into making a mistake so you'll
get a penalty. Wisniewski is flat-out dirty. He's trying to hurt
you, know what I'm saying?''
</P>
<P>
   4. Does the devil exist?
</P>
<P>
   ``Yes, there's truly a devil. There are evil spirits that lurk
on the dark side, and there is a chief of those evil spirits.''
</P>
<P>
   5. Would you go spend $7.50 to see ``End of Days,'' a movie in
which Arnold Schwarzenegger's character is confronted by the devil?
</P>
<P>
   ``I might go see it. I don't have a problem with a movie like
that because I've seen that kind of stuff for real. So to me, that
wouldn't be a big deal, as long as you stay prayed up.''
</P>
<P>
   6. The last good movie you did see?
</P>
<P>
   ``''Blue Streak'' with Martin Lawrence.''
</P>
<P>
   7. Do athletes have a responsibility as role models to children?
</P>
<P>
   ``''Athletes responsible?'' We are not responsible for nothing!
I hope to God that no parent tells his or her children to be like
any athlete. One, they never see us in person. Two, what we do on
Sunday is just an act. We do it very well, but it's an act.
Quarterbacks don't walk down the street saying `hut' and defensive
linemen don't walk down the street tackling people. No, I don't
think athletes should ever be put in the light of role models for
children. In my opinion, the only athlete who has been able to do
that _ even he faltered a little bit _ is Michael Jordan.''
</P>
<P>
   8. You were Mike Ditka's last first-round draft pick in Chicago.
What was it like being a 20-year-old rookie in 1992 and playing for
Iron Mike?
</P>
<P>
   ``It was great. With Mike, there's not much middle ground.
Either you're a player he liked or a player that he didn't like at
all. I was a player he liked, so it was good for me.''
</P>
<P>
   9. How did you get the name Alonzo?
</P>
<P>
   ``My grandfather. Alonzo was his middle name.''
</P>
<P>
   10. Complete this sentence: The best quality I've gotten from my
mom is _____.
</P>
<P>
   ``Her faith. She has the faith of a giant.''
</P>
<P>
   11. You are 6-foot-4, 292 pounds and considered to be one of the
two or three strongest players on the Cowboys. Is there anyone in
your family close to your size?
</P>
<P>
   ``My father is 6-8. I still look up to him.''
</P>
<P>
   12. You wear a size 18 shoe. How many pairs do you own, and
where do you find them?
</P>
<P>
   ``I own about two or three pairs of dress shoes. I get them from
Atlanta, mail order. But I used to own 25 to 30 pairs of shoes at
one time. I gave them all away about a year ago to my cousins. My
cousins are not small.''
</P>
<P>
   13. Your musical preference?
</P>
<P>
   ``I stay away from music except in the weight room. On my own,
if I was going to listen to music, it would be gospel. What I do
listen to are the tapes of Bishop T.D. Jakes. I listen to him all
the time, every day, whenever I get in my car. That's like music to
me.''
</P>
<P>
   14. You meet an atheist. Do you pity him, ignore him or try to
convince him there is a God?
</P>
<P>
   ``None of those exactly. I would ``warn'' him. To tell an
atheist there is a God would be wasting my breath. But to warn him
... well, there would be no excuse for him later to say, `I didn't
know it was going to get this bad.' That's the direction I would
take.''
</P>
<P>
   15. How much time do you spend in the weight room?
</P>
<P>
   ``Four to eight hours a week.''
</P>
<P>
   16. How much time do you spend praying?
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm in constant prayer.''
</P>
<P>
   17. You are NFL commissioner for a day. What is your first order
of business to improve the league or make the game better?
</P>
<P>
   ``I would make it that all offensive linemen had to line up with
their feet on the ball. No more advantages.''
</P>
<P>
   18. If you could have anything in the world to eat, what would
it be and who would cook it?
</P>
<P>
   ``My mother's homemade baked macaroni and cheese. She has an
unbelievable recipe.''
</P>
<P>
   19. You fall asleep and dream. In your dream, you accomplish
something so exhilarating, so unimaginable, but it has nothing to
do with football. What did you dream?
</P>
<P>
   ``Definitely that I'm playing basketball at the pro level. Me
with about six more inches of height playing in the NBA ... that
would be a dream.''
</P>
<P>
   20. Your biggest pet peeve?
</P>
<P>
   ``The hard stuff around the top of toothpaste and mayonnaise,
anything like that.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
