<SLUG> BC-BKC-RUSH-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
REPORT: STANLEY SUED PIGGIE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The men involved in JaRon Rush's suspension are
reportedly at odds.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles sports agent Jerome Stanley has sued Myron Piggie,
Rush's former AAU coach, for $43,500 in unpaid loans, according to
a published report.
</P>
<P>
   Stanley's suit was filed earlier this year, according to the
Kansas City Star, and seeks payment on loans made to Piggie between
Aug. 1, 1997 and May 8, 1998. Rush was a senior at Pembroke Hill
School at the time.
</P>
<P>
   The loans were intended to help Piggie promote Stanley's
business.
</P>
<P>
   Rush reportedly received $200-$300 from Stanley, a violation of
the NCAA's extra-benefits rule. UCLA is also examining Rush's
financial relationship with Piggie, who's under federal
investigation for tax evasion and fraud.
</P>
<P>
   Piggie denied receiving the loans and said he and Stanley have
done nothing improper.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
