<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are considering for
Page 1, Monday, Dec. 20. The N.Y. Times News Service Supervisor is
Tim Hilchey; phone: (888) 346-9867.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-ELECT (Moscow) _ Centrist parties made major gains Sunday
in Russian parliamentary elections in an apparent breakthrough for
pro-reform groups, according to an exit poll. (Summary from wires.)
By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CHECHNYA (Mozdok, Russia) _ Mikhail A. Kashpurin is a
frail old man with years of valorous service in the Soviet army, an
unblemished labor record and a story to tell. It boils down to
this. He was in the wrong place at the wrong time. The place was
Grozny and the time was Russia's ongoing military campaign. By
Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CUBANS-PRISON-DEAL (Washington) _ U.S. officials secured the
release of seven hostages at a Louisiana prison on Sunday by
promising their captors safe passage to Cuba, sources close to the
negotiations said. (Summary from wires.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL-GENERAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TAILORMADE-MEDICINE (Cincinnati) _ Scientists believe humans
have hundreds of thousands of genetic variations, and drug
companies are avidly searching for them, convinced that they can
use collections of them to identify patients who will benefit from
drugs, patients who will not and patients who will suffer troubling
side effects. Eventually, they say, this research will lead them
into an era of tailor-made medicine. By Gina Kolata.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   DEMS-DEBATE (Washington) _ Vice President Al Gore said on Sunday
that he would halt all radio and television commercials in his
presidential campaign if Bill Bradley did the same, a challenge
that set off the most rancorous and personal exchanges thus far
between the two Democratic competitors. They appeared on NBC's
``Meet the Press'' television show. By Richard L. Berke.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   MONSANTO-DEAL (Chicago) _ Monsanto and Pharmacia &AMP; Upjohn are
expected to reach a merger that would create a $52 billion company.
By David Barboza.
</P>
