that he would halt all radio and television commercials in his
presidential campaign if Bill Bradley did the same, a challenge
that set off the most rancorous and personal exchanges thus far
between the two Democratic competitors. They appeared on NBC's
``Meet the Press'' television show. By Richard L. Berke.
