<HEADLINE>
SHAQ BE NIMBLE, SHAQ BE QUICK, SHAQ SHOOTS FREE THROWS LIKE ...
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Once upon a time there was a really big kid who
grew up to be a really big kid.
</P>
<P>
   He had many talents. But the best thing he could do was take a
basketball in his large hand, leap a few inches off the ground and
throw it through a hoop ring. People would come from miles and give
him bags of gold to watch him do this amazing feat.
</P>
<P>
   But the really big kid was unfulfilled. He wanted people to
respect him for other things besides playing with a ball and
complaining to referees. He sang songs and made CDs. He pretended
he was someone else and made movies. But the people didn't seem to
care.
</P>
<P>
   Then he decided to write a book, just for kids. He called it
``Shaq and the Beanstalk and Other Very Tall Tales'' (Scholastic
Cartwheel Books, $15.95, illustrated by Shane W. Evans). He told
fairy tales. Except he put himself in as the main character.
</P>
<P>
   It looked kind of self-serving. But the kids laughed as they
read about Little Red Riding Shaq. And Shaq and the Three Bears.
And Shaq's New Clothes. And Shaq and the Three Billy Goats Gruff.
</P>
<P>
   ``You think they are tall tales?'' Shaq asked at the end of his
book. ``Well, OK, sure. Maybe I did s-t-r-e-t-c-h the truth a bit.
Maybe they are tall tales. But hey, what do you expect from a guy
who is over seven feet tall? Short tales?! I don't think so!''
</P>
<P>
   That made the kids laugh again.
</P>
<P>
   Shaq likes people to laugh with him, not at him. And this book
does just that.
</P>
<P>
   So the moral of this story: When you do something to help
programs like Reading is Fundamental, the Boys and Girls Clubs of
America, Athletes &AMP; Entertainers for Kids, City of Hope and
California Mentoring Initiative _ which is to get kids to read _
Shaq comes out a very, very big man indeed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-19-99 2014EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
