<HEADLINE>
`OH XMAS TREE, OH XMAS TREE, WITHOUT HONG KONG, WHERE WOULD WE
BE?'  
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN. EDITORS: Timely for Christmas!...RESENDING from Dec. 11)   (This 350-word Christmas-time ``separate-buy'' article is from the
11 Dec. 1999 issue of The ECONOMIST magazine.)  
  
