<SLUG> BC--BUDGET-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   These are the stories The San Francisco Chronicle Business
section plans to move for Monday, December 20, on the New York
Times wire. For questions, please call Terry Nagel at 415-777-6268
or the business desk at 415-536-5172. For business stories running
in main news, call the news desk at 415-777-7074.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CHARITY _ &LR;  A dizzying array of for-profit companies are
offering to funnel money to nonprofit organizations, from charity
malls and custom portal creators. This report tells how to sort
through the dozens of new companies, how to confirm that a gift
really gets to the organization and whether participation in these
schemes is tax-deductible. With sidebars on Hunger Site and tips
from the Better Business Bureau. By CARRIE KIRBY.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PRONTO _ &LR;  High-speed DSL access to the Internet is out of reach
for millions of Californians in rural and even some suburban
communities because the technology is distance limited. That's
about to change. SBC Communications, the Texas-based parent of Pac
Bell, recently announced plans to invest $6 billion in a program to
extend the reach of its DSL service. By PETER KUPFER.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BIOSCOPE _ &LR;  Genentech is riding high with its stock soaring and
a revolutionary asthma drug in the works. By TOM ABATE
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OUTTAKES _  &LR; The ASCI White installation at the Lawrence
Livermore National Laboratory is expected to be the world's fastest
supercomputer. By JAN BOYD and STAN BUNGER.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CARTOON _  &LR; A Silicon Valley venture capitalist and his wife, an
illustrator, poke fun at venture capitalists in their new comic
book, ``The VC _ The Surreal World of Silicon Valley Venture
Capital.'' By CARRIE KIRBY.
</P>
</TEXT>
